1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,692
Three days ago OpenAI pushed a silent update

2
00:00:03,692 --> 00:00:07,384
to their API. No press release. No tweet

3
00:00:07,384 --> 00:00:11,076
storm. Just a changelog entry that most developers

4
00:00:11,076 --> 00:00:12,000
scrolled past.

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,428
Every six months we get a new model

6
00:00:15,428 --> 00:00:18,857
and everyone says it changes everything. This time

7
00:00:18,857 --> 00:00:22,285
the benchmark numbers are not the story. The

8
00:00:22,285 --> 00:00:25,714
story is the price drop. GPT-4 level reasoning

9
00:00:25,714 --> 00:00:29,142
now costs ninety-five percent less than it did

10
00:00:29,142 --> 00:00:30,000
in 2023.

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,571
I pulled the financials. Klarna replaced seven hundred

12
00:00:34,571 --> 00:00:39,142
customer service agents. Duolingo cut their contractor headcount

13
00:00:39,142 --> 00:00:43,714
by fifty percent. These are not startups —

14
00:00:43,714 --> 00:00:48,285
these are companies with billions in revenue making

15
00:00:48,285 --> 00:00:50,000
hard decisions fast.

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,459
The jobs at risk are not the ones

17
00:00:53,459 --> 00:00:56,918
you expect. It is not factory workers. It

18
00:00:56,918 --> 00:01:00,378
is paralegals, junior analysts, content writers, tier-one support.

19
00:01:00,378 --> 00:01:03,837
Basically anyone whose job is to read something

20
00:01:03,837 --> 00:01:06,000
and produce a structured output.

21
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,599
But here is the thing nobody is saying

22
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:13,200
loudly enough. Every wave of automation creates more

23
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:16,799
jobs than it destroys — eventually. The question

24
00:01:16,799 --> 00:01:20,400
is whether you are positioned on the creation

25
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:24,000
side or the destruction side of that curve.

26
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,911
Pick one repetitive task in your workflow. Could

27
00:01:27,911 --> 00:01:31,822
be writing reports, summarising emails, triaging tickets. Automate

28
00:01:31,822 --> 00:01:35,733
it with the API this weekend. Not because

29
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:39,644
your job is at risk right now. Because

30
00:01:39,644 --> 00:01:43,555
the muscle memory of building with AI is

31
00:01:43,555 --> 00:01:46,000
the actual skill that compounds.
